title: PPPP’s Irfan Ali Laghari wins NA-227 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) candidate Irfan Ali Laghari has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-227 Dadu-I by securing 104,013 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Grand Democratic Alliance candidate Liaqat Ali Jatoi, who bagged 93,956 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.66 percent.
